==Messages==
{{message|You hear crashing rock.|Produced {{frac|5}} of the time when a monster tunnels through a rock [[wall]].}}
{{message|You feel an unexpected draft.|Produced {{frac|3}} of the time when a monster tunnels through a [[door]].}}
{{message|&lt;Monster&gt; digs in.|Produced when a pet umber hulk, woodchuck, or rock mole eats something off the ground in your sight. This [[YAFM]] replaces the ordinary pet eating message.{{refsrc|dogmove.c|271|nethack=3.6.0}}}}

==Technical details==
Monsters that can tunnel have the [[M1_TUNNEL]] monster attribute. Monsters that require picks and axes also have the [[M1_NEEDPICK]] monster attribute in addition to M1_TUNNEL. No monster in vanilla [[NetHack]] has M1_NEEDPICK but not M1_TUNNEL.

